abstract: The juice blend, sold under the Minute Maid brand, is made almost entirely from apple and grape juice but is called Pomegranate Blueberry.
snippet: The juice blend, sold under the Minute Maid brand, is made almost entirely from apple and grape juice but is called Pomegranate Blueberry.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court on Thursday unanimously allowed a false advertising suit against a Coca-Cola juice blend to move forward, saying the company’s practices “allegedly mislead and trick consumers, all to the injury of competitors.”

abstract: Assisted living facilities are just beginning to grapple with the questions raised by intimate relations among residents, including those with cognitive impairment.
snippet: Assisted living facilities are just beginning to grapple with the questions raised by intimate relations among residents, including those with cognitive impairment.
lead_paragraph: Trulah Goin Mills had developed dementia and couldn’t be left alone in the house, but when she and her husband, Lewis, moved into an assisted living facility in Boise, Idaho, in 2012, one lifelong quality remained intact.

abstract: In “The Antiquarian,” the narrator’s best friend, confined to a psychiatric ward after the murder of his fiancée, admits to the deed yet drops hints that the truth might be more complex.
snippet: In “The Antiquarian,” the narrator’s best friend, confined to a psychiatric ward after the murder of his fiancée, admits to the deed yet drops hints that the truth might be more complex.
lead_paragraph: The news from college friends tends to be the stuff of weddings, children and jobs. In “The Antiquarian,” the delightfully macabre first novel by the Peruvian writer Gustavo Faverón Patriau, the narrator, Gustavo, receives a rather more alarming update: His closest friend from his university days, Daniel, has murdered his fiancée, Juliana, by stabbing her 36 times, attempting to burn her body and leaving her in the trunk of his car while trying to kill himself with a gunshot to the head. He fails and lands in a psychiatric ward.

abstract: A capable, utilitarian crossover with more power than the base model, the XV Crosstrek Hybrid will not turn in impressive fuel-economy numbers.
snippet: A capable, utilitarian crossover with more power than the base model, the XV Crosstrek Hybrid will not turn in impressive fuel-economy numbers.
lead_paragraph: Subaru and Prius owners are fiercely loyal to their rides. Subie drivers (who often dwell in polar vortex regions) pledge their allegiance to the Symmetrical All-Wheel Drive flag. The evangelical hybrid camp is more obsessed with fuel economy than getting places quickly. Conversely, it’s unwise to off-road a Prius, and the only way to guarantee lofty m.p.g.s in a Subaru is coasting from a mountain summit.
headline_main: Video: The Subaru XV Crosstrek Hybrid Won’t Save Much Green

abstract: The roughly 2,000 documents cover subjects including Rwanda, policies toward gays in the military, the Oklahoma City bombing and Vice President Al Gore’s presidential campaign.
snippet: The roughly 2,000 documents cover subjects including Rwanda, policies toward gays in the military, the Oklahoma City bombing and Vice President Al Gore’s presidential campaign.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The National Archives unsealed about 2,000 documents from the Clinton administration on Friday, the fifth such release in recent months of memos, transcripts and speeches that had been withheld from public view.

abstract: “The Case Against 8” documents the same-sex-marriage case that took four years to wind its way to the Supreme Court.
snippet: “The Case Against 8” documents the same-sex-marriage case that took four years to wind its way to the Supreme Court.
lead_paragraph: As gay men living in California, Ben Cotner and Ryan White were “flabbergasted,” Mr. White recalled, by the passage of Proposition 8, their state’s 2008 ballot measure to deny the right of same-sex couples to marry. They didn’t expect it to win.

abstract: A flourishing arts scene in the capital city, Kigali, is bringing healing and reconciliation 20 years after the genocide.
snippet: A flourishing arts scene in the capital city, Kigali, is bringing healing and reconciliation 20 years after the genocide.
lead_paragraph: “There’s no way you’ll find it yourself,” the artist Strong Karakire told me on the phone, when I asked for directions to his studio in Nyamirambo, a lively neighborhood in the Rwandan capital of Kigali where dirt roads climb the steep hills past modest dwellings. “Just wait at the petrol station, and I’ll come get you.”

abstract: New thrillers include Mo Hayder’s “Wolf” and Jo Nesbo’s “The Son.”
snippet: New thrillers include Mo Hayder’s “Wolf” and Jo Nesbo’s “The Son.”
lead_paragraph: I had the wrong idea about beach books. It came from “Goodbye, Columbus,” where Neil Klugman tells Brenda Patimkin that his cousin Doris always has “War and Peace” by the pool: “That’s how I know it’s the summer, when Doris is reading ‘War and Peace.’ ” Pool and beach being the same to me back then — an idiot kid forced to sit outside with no TV, uncomfortable with my shirt off as my grandfather paraded around to show off he still had a body — I didn’t see that Philip Roth was mocking Doris, and so for years protected myself from the water and sand I resented and feared by lugging along a classic. This is how I read “Swann’s Way” at the Mamaroneck Beach Club as a guest of Uncle Marty and Aunt Lee. It took many visits. Here I would like to thank them personally.
